# MITRE ATT&CK: T1583.001, T1588.003, T1027.002
# Context: Iranian actors consistently use European VPS, .online TLDs,
#          SSH key reuse, standardized HTTP 404 responses, Themida packing,
#          UPX modifications, polyglot files
#==============================================================================

# Iranian infrastructure - .online TLD resolution
# TUNING NOTE: .online is a legitimate gTLD with millions of registrations.
# This rule fires on ANY .online DNS query. In most environments this will be
# extremely noisy. Recommended: disable unless correlated with other Iranian
# APT indicators via flowbits. Threshold raised to 50/hour to reduce noise.
alert dns $HOME_NET any -> any any (msg:"Bark&Bite - Iranian APT Suspicious .online TLD Resolution 2026"; dns.query; content:".online"; endswith; threshold:type both, track by_src, count 50, seconds 3600; classtype:bad-unknown; sid:2000284; rev:2; metadata:policy max-detect-ips drop, created_at 2026_03_12, updated_at 2026_04_07;)

