#==============================================================================
# SECTION 39: PRAYER APP COMPROMISE AND MOBILE TARGETING
# MITRE ATT&CK: T1444, T1437
# Context: CloudSEK Mar 2026 - Muslim prayer-time app exploited with
#          political messaging via push notifications; mobile targeting
#          via trojanized Starlink VPN apps (DCHSpy)
#==============================================================================

# Trojanized APK download via bit.ly shortened URLs (common delivery method)
# FP reduction (rev 2): added threshold — bare bit.ly matching is too broad
# for production. Threshold limits to 10 unique bit.ly requests per source
# per hour, which is still useful for burst delivery campaigns while reducing
# noise from legitimate bit.ly usage.
alert http $HOME_NET any -> $EXTERNAL_NET any (msg:"Bark&Bite - Iranian APT Shortened URL APK Delivery 2026"; flow:to_server,established; content:"GET"; http_method; content:"bit.ly"; http_host; threshold:type both, track by_src, count 10, seconds 3600; classtype:social-engineering; sid:2000315; rev:2; metadata:policy max-detect-ips drop, created_at 2026_03_12, updated_at 2026_04_05;)

